A **flexi deposit** (also called multi-option deposit or MOD) is a type of FD where you can withdraw in parts without breaking the entire FD. The remaining amount continues to earn FD interest. It is offered by most major banks as an alternative to standard FDs, giving you liquidity while still earning better than savings account rates.
